    {
      "id": "d1fbd0468d799230682ddc45caaa7cd40ec7dfbf",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 101,
        "name": "Lai Siyao",
        "email": "lai.siyao@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "laisiyao"
      },
      "date": "2018-09-12 08:11:49.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2: Code-Review-1\n\nMike, maybe it's better to fix it instead of just revert it, since it's hard to reproduce and not a blocker to autotest.\n\nIMHO, the quick fix is to add ldlm_set_cbpending() if BL ast not really sent for local locks, so that client can cancel this lock upon decref. And it looks fine to set CBPENDING here, for mdt_blocking_ast() --> ldlm_blocking_ast_nocheck() set this flag always even there is still reader or writer.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "77f4bf6a839ca8fec47156024f9fd7e94389bdde",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 118,
        "name": "Mikhail Pershin",
        "email": "mpershin@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "tappro"
      },
      "date": "2018-09-12 17:33:36.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nLai, I agree that it is better to fix it without revert, but I think it is not enough to use just cbpending flag. I have to think how that will affect lock convert code, if you don't mind I can care about that and prepare a fix",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "0e563e982b9f7640de77e6afaec986a328299696",
      "author": {
